Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.52,0:00:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.05,0:00:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.75,0:00:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about the technical
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.76,0:00:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulties, but we're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.89,0:00:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughing] All right, so I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.16,0:00:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sarah Roddy and welcome to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Localizing with Xcode 9 session.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.51,0:00:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, with my colleagues Ia
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.01,0:00:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and Chris, who would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.24,0:00:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,talk to you about some exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.06,0:00:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,new improvements we made to the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.27,0:00:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,localization process in Xcode 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.91,0:00:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.70,0:00:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the world, you have so
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.79,0:00:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,many people who are looking to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.51,0:00:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,access and use your great
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.13,0:00:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,applications, but they can't do
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.21,0:00:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you don't give them the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.67,0:00:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,ability to use your apps in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.53,0:00:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,their native language.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.29,0:00:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And your app can easily access
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.21,0:01:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,this global audience by
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.83,0:01:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,following some simple steps and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.52,0:01:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,best practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.62,0:01:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in today's session, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.36,0:01:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about how Xcode makes it so
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.67,0:01:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,easy for you to add new
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.25,0:01:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,languages to make your app look
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.73,0:01:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel local, which will allow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.38,0:01:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you to go global.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.20,0:01:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are three main topics
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.15,0:01:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we will be covering today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.96,0:01:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we will start with how to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.73,0:01:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,make your code world ready, then
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.81,0:01:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we will walk you through the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.73,0:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,localization process in Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and introduce new features we
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.36,0:01:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,added in Xcode 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.96,0:01:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, and through the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.01,0:01:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation, we will talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.87,0:01:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,testing and give you some best
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.44,0:01:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,practices to make sure that your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.12,0:01:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,app works and looks great in all
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.43,0:01:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,languages that you support.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.93,0:01:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's start with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.04,0:01:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.05,0:01:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So internationalization is the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.74,0:01:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,process of designing your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.30,0:01:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,software so it can be adapted to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.44,0:01:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,different languages and regions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.81,0:01:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,without making code changes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.35,0:01:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,every single time you are adding
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.34,0:02:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a new language to your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.68,0:02:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the point here is it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.94,0:02:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't matter which language
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.94,0:02:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is running in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.80,0:02:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If the language has short text
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.17,0:02:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or long text or tall text or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.20,0:02:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,even text or layout that flows
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.34,0:02:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from right to left, your app
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.39,0:02:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,should be able to adapt
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamically to all these
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.11,0:02:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.20,0:02:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first step in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.00,0:02:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization is managing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.46,0:02:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,your strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.79,0:02:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Your app will be localized by
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.01,0:02:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,translators who would be working
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.04,0:02:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with your strings and in this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.38,0:02:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,localized string is there to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.70,0:02:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,make it easier for you to create
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.96,0:02:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable content for your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.71,0:02:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,translators as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.23,0:02:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,displaying the right text at the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.82,0:02:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.12,0:02:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So if your strings are coming
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.80,0:02:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,from a storyboard or a zip file
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.04,0:02:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they're localizable by default,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.38,0:02:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so we don't need to worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.54,0:02:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,those.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes you might have
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,some strings that are defined in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.43,0:02:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,your source code that will be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.86,0:02:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed to the user, like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:02:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,error messages or notifications;
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.34,0:03:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if you would like to notify your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,users about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.04,0:03:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this translator is also
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.50,0:03:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.72,0:03:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that you just need to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.11,0:03:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,wrap those strings with NS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.88,0:03:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Localized String.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.79,0:03:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to that you can use
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.01,0:03:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,NS Localized String as a format
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.05,0:03:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,string with localized language
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.25,0:03:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,format to get a localized and a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.20,0:03:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,formatted string.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So here let's go through a quick
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.39,0:03:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,example together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.28,0:03:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So here they have a label.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.18,0:03:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When I set its text to a string
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,called population.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.20,0:03:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So again, my string is hardcoded
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and is not localizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To make it localizable, you just
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.97,0:03:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,need to wrap it with NS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.52,0:03:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Localized String.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.62,0:03:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you can see here on the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.84,0:03:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,screen, NS Localized String
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.65,0:03:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,takes two arguments, your string
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.02,0:03:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and a comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.38,0:03:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Comments here are really, really
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.98,0:03:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,important to provide to your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.16,0:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,translators so they have context
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.09,0:03:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,about the string they are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.30,0:03:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,translating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would say most of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.11,0:03:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you just need to use NS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.52,0:03:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Localized String, but in some
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.67,0:03:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,cases when you're working on a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,framework or a shared component
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.11,0:04:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you might want to use NS
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.64,0:04:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Localized String from table
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.48,0:04:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,where you specify the table name
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.29,0:04:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,where your strings are coming
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.41,0:04:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I mentioned before, you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.53,0:04:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,can also combine NS Localized
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.43,0:04:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,String with Localized String
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.46,0:04:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,with Format, where NS Localized
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.18,0:04:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,String is a format string.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.46,0:04:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this case it's really,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.91,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,really critical that you provide
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,those comments for your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.31,0:04:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,translators so they have context
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.35,0:04:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,about the string they are
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.66,0:04:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,translating.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.34,0:04:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at run time NS Localized
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,String will determine the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.18,0:04:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,preferred language of the user
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.69,0:04:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and find the corresponding
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.60,0:04:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable string files.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.51,0:04:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see here, this is an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,example of a localizable string
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.99,0:04:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,files coming from the French
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,localization projects and it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.76,0:04:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,contains all your localizable
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.31,0:04:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,strings, the one that you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.27,0:04:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,wrapped with NS Localized String
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.23,0:04:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the comments that you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,provided.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.90,0:04:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the information that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.90,0:04:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will be provided to your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.59,0:04:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,translator.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're using Objective
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.20,0:05:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Senior App you can run the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.94,0:05:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,static analyzer to find
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.74,0:05:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,localizability problems in your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,code, like if you forgot to make
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.80,0:05:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a string localizable or if you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.52,0:05:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,forgot to add a comment to a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable string you can run
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.36,0:05:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the static analyzer and you get
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.78,0:05:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,warnings that will show you what
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.53,0:05:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,these problems are and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.97,0:05:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,fix them right on your code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to learn more
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.79,0:05:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,about the static analyzer please
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.40,0:05:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,check out this talk from last
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.89,0:05:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.13,0:05:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing that your app
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.51,0:05:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,should handle well when it comes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.10,0:05:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to localization is working with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.13,0:05:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,different visual representations
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of date, time, numbers, et
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.57,0:05:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.93,0:05:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, 12-hour time format
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.75,0:05:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is a standard format we use here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.72,0:05:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the US, but you want to make
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.47,0:05:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sure that a user who's using
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.56,0:05:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your app in France, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.88,0:05:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is getting 24-hour time
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.32,0:05:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,formatting set because this is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.69,0:05:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the default format used there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.17,0:05:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we provide a variety of very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.09,0:05:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful formatters that will
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,let you handle the complexity of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.17,0:06:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,data formatting and regions, but
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.57,0:06:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,just to give you an example on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.83,0:06:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,how formatters work, let's take
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.47,0:06:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a look at a date formatter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.73,0:06:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,example.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.05,0:06:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So here let's say you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.35,0:06:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,display a full date format in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.45,0:06:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.28,0:06:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of setting a date
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.14,0:06:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,format string that is specific
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.84,0:06:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to a region or a country that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.77,0:06:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,has a specific order, we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.75,0:06:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,recommend that you use date
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.57,0:06:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,style.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This formatter has different
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.40,0:06:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,styles that you can choose from,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but since here we want to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.30,0:06:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,display a full date format I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.96,0:06:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,setting my date style to full.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.69,0:06:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So with that you are making sure
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.07,0:06:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that your date is formatted
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.55,0:06:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly in all regions in the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.69,0:06:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.50,0:06:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see on the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there are differences between
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.23,0:06:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the date format in the US and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.81,0:06:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the date format in France, like
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.14,0:06:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the French date does not have
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.36,0:06:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,any commas, the month name is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.08,0:06:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not capitalized, the day of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.88,0:06:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,month comes before the month
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.06,0:06:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,itself, and this would not be
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.53,0:07:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,achievable if you have pasted in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.32,0:07:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a date format instead of a date
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.86,0:07:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,style.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to date formatter,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.92,0:07:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a series of formatters
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.18,0:07:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for common data types available
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.98,0:07:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.10,0:07:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to learn more
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.23,0:07:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,about formatters please check
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,out these two great talks from
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.63,0:07:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.17,0:07:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, you want to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.24,0:07:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that your user interface is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.73,0:07:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,flexible and looks nice and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.48,0:07:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful in all languages that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.99,0:07:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you support and to do that the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.17,0:07:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,process is really simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need to use base
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization and auto
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.19,0:07:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's talk about base
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.49,0:07:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization for a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.66,0:07:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So by enabling base
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.20,0:07:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization in your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.58,0:07:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,project, Xcode modifies your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.14,0:07:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,projects for Destructor and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.00,0:07:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,separates your UI from your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.29,0:07:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,strings, which means any file
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.13,0:07:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that is related to your user
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.53,0:07:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,interface, like a zip file or a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.90,0:07:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboard file, will be stored
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:07:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in base [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.60,0:08:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,While your strings, either if
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.38,0:08:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they are coming from a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.18,0:08:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboard file or if they are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.89,0:08:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in your code that you wrapped
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.98,0:08:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with NS Localized String, they
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,will be stored in the specific
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.32,0:08:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,language folders so that way you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.43,0:08:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,only have one set of user
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.98,0:08:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,interface instead of duplicating
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.15,0:08:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,your UI every single time you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.57,0:08:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are creating a new language in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.85,0:08:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And base internationalization is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,enabled by default since Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.31,0:08:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,5.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.75,0:08:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have an older project
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.17,0:08:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to localize,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.55,0:08:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,please make sure that you enable
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.81,0:08:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.05,0:08:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you might be already
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.96,0:08:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with auto layout or
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you're already using it to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.97,0:08:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,support different presentations
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.06,0:08:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of your app or different screen
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes, but auto layout is also a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,critical technology to use for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.30,0:08:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.76,0:08:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So by using auto layout you are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.36,0:08:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,making sure that your app is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,flexible and it can adapt to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.58,0:08:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,different string lengths and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.70,0:08:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,different configurations of your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.74,0:08:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.86,0:09:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And new in Xcode 9 we are
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.87,0:09:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,introducing new interface
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,builder localization warnings to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.48,0:09:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,validate your constraints for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.11,0:09:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,localization, which means when
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.30,0:09:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you are working on your UI and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.19,0:09:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your storyboard file or your zip
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.63,0:09:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,file and you're setting up these
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.87,0:09:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints and they are not
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.35,0:09:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,localization friendly you will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.05,0:09:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,get this warning as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.62,0:09:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,suggestions on how to fix them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.40,0:09:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And new interface builder
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.56,0:09:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,warnings will be available in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.34,0:09:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the future seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.68,0:09:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally we are introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.73,0:09:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,an Xcode -- 9 used to the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.17,0:09:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,localization options for you to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.38,0:09:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,simulate a localized
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.58,0:09:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.61,0:09:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of having a real
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.47,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,strings, translated strings, to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,see how they look like in your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.00,0:09:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,app you can just use one of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,these pseudo localization
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.77,0:09:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,options that we are providing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in Xcode 9, we have new
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.90,0:09:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,options for accented Latin
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.42,0:09:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,strings for a fixed strings and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.37,0:09:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,new options for right to left
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.60,0:09:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.79,0:09:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,call Ia on stage to give you a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.24,0:09:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,demo about how to prepare your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.86,0:09:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,app for localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:09:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.52,0:10:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.10,0:10:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.63,0:10:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. I'm Ia and today I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.58,0:10:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,show you this really cool app
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.14,0:10:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been working on called
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.27,0:10:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,International Effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.03,0:10:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see on the screen, my UI
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,consists mostly of this table
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.08,0:10:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,view and a user can go and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.15,0:10:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,select a country or territory
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.95,0:10:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,from this list and they'll see
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.91,0:10:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,some information about it like
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.13,0:10:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the flag, the population, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.78,0:10:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,even the language population.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.57,0:10:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So I made sure my app looks
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.05,0:10:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful in English and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.39,0:10:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,happy with the way it looks, but
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.65,0:10:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,now I want to internationalize
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.47,0:10:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it so it can be ready for my
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.88,0:10:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,first localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.86,0:10:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,follow the steps that Sarah just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,showed us in her slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.62,0:10:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first thing I want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.94,0:10:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is my strings management.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.10,0:10:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm loading all of these strings
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.02,0:10:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in my table cells in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:10:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to open my Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.58,0:10:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,project.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.55,0:11:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And in my table view controller,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.74,0:11:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in my cell for wrote indexpath
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.65,0:11:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,function I want to make sure I
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.59,0:11:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have any hardcoded strings
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.37,0:11:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm loading into my UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.41,0:11:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead I want to replace
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.27,0:11:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,them with a call to NS Localized
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.59,0:11:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,String.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.61,0:11:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll pass in my English
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.77,0:11:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,string and I'll also give a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.40,0:11:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So; "Label preceding the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.77,0:11:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,selected territory."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.80,0:11:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I also went ahead and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.33,0:11:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,made sure I'm calling NS
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.65,0:11:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Localized String for all the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.34,0:11:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,other text I'm loading in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.75,0:11:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next thing I want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.59,0:11:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is I also want to make sure I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.67,0:11:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,displaying and representing data
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.24,0:11:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly for different locales.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.48,0:11:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this case my data are
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.41,0:11:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,mostly these numbers that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.09,0:11:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing on the right side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.65,0:11:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And numbers are displayed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.96,0:11:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,differently in different
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.97,0:11:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.51,0:11:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So to format them correctly I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.33,0:11:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,going to use a number formatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.53,0:12:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Number formatter is similar to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.60,0:12:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,date formatter that Sarah showed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.98,0:12:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,us earlier, except, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.76,0:12:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's used to format numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.57,0:12:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.30,0:12:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So for population I can simply
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.32,0:12:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,set my formatter's number style
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.98,0:12:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to decimal and I set "uses
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.07,0:12:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,grouping separator" to "true,"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.90,0:12:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which makes it easier to read by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.43,0:12:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,separating the number by the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.64,0:12:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands, and that's because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.94,0:12:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,population tends to be a large
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.45,0:12:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,number.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For GDP I can also use a number
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.25,0:12:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,formatter, except this time I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,would set the number style to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,currency and the currency code
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.40,0:12:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to US dollars because our data
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.90,0:12:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is in US dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.88,0:12:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, for the literacy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,percentage cell, as well as my
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.67,0:12:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,language population, I set the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.70,0:12:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,number style to percent and I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.91,0:12:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,give it a maximum and minimum
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,fraction digits to make sure it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.90,0:12:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,looks consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.22,0:12:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that my strings are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.27,0:12:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable and I'm displaying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.21,0:12:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,my numbers -- and I'm formatting
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.82,0:13:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,my numbers correctly, the next
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.73,0:13:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thing I want to do is make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.16,0:13:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,my user interface is also ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.86,0:13:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that I'm going to open
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.52,0:13:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,my main storyboard and I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.23,0:13:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,show you how you can use pseudo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.53,0:13:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,languages in Interface Builder
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.32,0:13:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Preview to test your app for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.67,0:13:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.24,0:13:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So first I'll click on the top
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.99,0:13:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,right corner on the Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.77,0:13:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor icon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.78,0:13:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then under this dropdown I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.54,0:13:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,want to choose "preview" and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.08,0:13:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,basically it's showing me a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.33,0:13:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,preview of my storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.86,0:13:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the bottom, right corner
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.61,0:13:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I get a language chooser and if
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.44,0:13:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I had any localizations on my
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.76,0:13:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,project I would see those here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.22,0:13:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but in this case it's showing me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.43,0:13:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,all the pseudo language options
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.23,0:13:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can use in the preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.29,0:13:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So new in Xcode 9 we've
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.52,0:13:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced a fixed pseudo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.85,0:13:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,language.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.23,0:13:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to select that to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.49,0:13:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,see what it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.33,0:13:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see it simply added
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.81,0:13:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,those square brackets and the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.23,0:13:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,pound symbol before and after
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.78,0:13:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,each string.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.61,0:14:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And that makes it really easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.17,0:14:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,spot if something is clipping or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.74,0:14:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,not fitting in my UI because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.57,0:14:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,those symbols would be missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.45,0:14:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this case it looks like my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.71,0:14:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,button on the bottom doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.01,0:14:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,have the pound symbol and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.32,0:14:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing I saw, but if
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.86,0:14:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you take a closer look, even --
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.10,0:14:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the y is clipping in "play."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.65,0:14:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to go back to my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboard and see why that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.16,0:14:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks like I have a fixed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.61,0:14:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,width constraint, which in this
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.20,0:14:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,case is not necessary and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.66,0:14:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,generally fixed width
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.92,0:14:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints on text controls are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.94,0:14:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a bad idea for localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.57,0:14:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I get rid of it you'll see
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that my pseudo language looks
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.47,0:14:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly as expected and now I
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.64,0:14:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,know that I'm not going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.30,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,clipping anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.24,0:14:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So these interface builder
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.56,0:14:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,previews are even more helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.19,0:14:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have more of your UI
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.41,0:14:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,defined in your storyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.47,0:14:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In my case, a lot of my UI is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.44,0:14:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,loaded in my table view
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.62,0:14:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.78,0:14:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I also want to show how I can
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.47,0:14:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,use pseudo languages at runtime
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.29,0:14:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to test that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.72,0:15:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I select -- if I click on
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.53,0:15:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,my scheme and select "edit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.47,0:15:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,scheme" -- and make sure you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.47,0:15:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have "run" selected in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,sidebar -- under "application
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.86,0:15:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,language" you get a list of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.95,0:15:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,languages you can choose from,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.78,0:15:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but over at the bottom you have
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.13,0:15:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a list of all the available
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.02,0:15:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,pseudo languages you can use as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.60,0:15:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,well -- at runtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.68,0:15:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Another pseudo language we've
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.80,0:15:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,added in Xcode 9 is the accented
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.83,0:15:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Latin pseudo language.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.66,0:15:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I go ahead and play that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.48,0:15:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.23,0:15:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My app will launch with accents
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.93,0:15:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,above and below each of my
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.56,0:15:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.30,0:15:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And what this really helps with
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.81,0:15:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is it gives me a preview of what
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.45,0:15:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my app -- how my app would
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,handle languages that use a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of accents, diacritics, or even
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.29,0:15:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,languages where the scripted
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.10,0:15:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,self is generally taller than
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.80,0:15:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,English -- like Thai for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.97,0:15:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,example.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.10,0:15:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can quickly scan this and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.79,0:15:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that everything's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.33,0:16:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,fitting vertically and I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.06,0:16:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing any clippings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.97,0:16:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything looks good here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.39,0:16:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then finally one more pseudo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,language I'd like to show you at
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.74,0:16:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,runtime is the new right to left
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.67,0:16:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,pseudo language with right to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.86,0:16:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,left strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.88,0:16:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And this pseudo language is very
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.42,0:16:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful in testing whether your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.73,0:16:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,app is ready for right to left
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.87,0:16:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,languages like Arabic and Hebrew
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.96,0:16:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,where the text itself is written
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.32,0:16:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,from right to left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.66,0:16:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you can see, my UI
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.10,0:16:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,controls are already adjusted
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.87,0:16:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and mirrored to look the way
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.41,0:16:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they would look in a right to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.37,0:16:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,left localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we also do is we
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.61,0:16:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,display the localizable strings
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.41,0:16:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from right to left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So the letters themselves have
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.95,0:16:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,flipped order and that really
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.82,0:16:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,helps give you an idea -- or put
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.47,0:16:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you in the mindset of somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.84,0:16:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,who reads their text from right
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.62,0:16:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.06,0:16:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are some of the pseudo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.81,0:16:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.52,0:16:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I highly encourage you to try
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.89,0:16:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.51,0:16:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They're very helpful to test
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.95,0:16:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your app before you even add
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.43,0:16:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.46,0:17:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And to summarize the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.45,0:17:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization process;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.87,0:17:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,first make sure you're using
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.60,0:17:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,standard APIs to load
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.08,0:17:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable strings as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to format your data, like dates
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.73,0:17:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.84,0:17:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And make sure your app is using
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.44,0:17:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,base internationalization to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.11,0:17:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,separate your UI from your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.87,0:17:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable content.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, use auto layout
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in your UI to make sure that the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.53,0:17:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,app itself is flexible and can
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.88,0:17:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,adapt to different translations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.50,0:17:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And, finally, we showed a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.26,0:17:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,tools that can validate your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.71,0:17:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization, like the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.02,0:17:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,new pseudo languages we've added
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.66,0:17:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the auto layout warnings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.68,0:17:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that are coming soon in the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.82,0:17:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,future seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.56,0:17:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So my app is internationalized
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.75,0:17:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,now and I'm ready to add my
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.39,0:17:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,first localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.43,0:17:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to call Sarah back
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.29,0:17:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,up on stage to show us how to do
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.04,0:17:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that since she's the expert on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.60,0:17:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.52,0:18:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.05,0:18:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Ia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.37,0:18:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that you're done with the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.75,0:18:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,steps that Ia showed us earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.28,0:18:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in her demo, you are ready to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.98,0:18:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,add new languages to your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.96,0:18:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do that right from
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.53,0:18:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode from your project info and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.51,0:18:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you have over 100 languages to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.50,0:18:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,choose from.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.07,0:18:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that you've added these
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.31,0:18:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,languages that you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.62,0:18:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,support in your app, so to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.38,0:18:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,generate the localizable content
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.25,0:18:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for your translators Xcode will
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.51,0:18:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,find all the localizable
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.20,0:18:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,resources that you have in your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.96,0:18:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,project, then when you export
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.93,0:18:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,your projects for localization
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.87,0:18:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode will extract the strings
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.85,0:18:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from this localizable resources
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.86,0:18:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and generate XLIFF files for
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.99,0:18:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,every single language that you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.33,0:18:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,have added.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.49,0:18:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And XLIFF file is simply a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.18,0:18:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,standard XML localization file
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.55,0:18:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,format that is standard in the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,localization industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.83,0:18:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you send your XLIFF files
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.62,0:18:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to one of the localizers they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.08,0:18:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will be already familiar with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.52,0:18:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the formats and how to work with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.96,0:18:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.28,0:18:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So once your XLIFF files are
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.59,0:18:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,translated you can import them
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.55,0:19:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,back and Xcode will integrate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically your localized
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.72,0:19:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,text back into your project.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.05,0:19:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the localization
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.44,0:19:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,process in Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.02,0:19:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.23,0:19:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And new in Xcode 9 we are adding
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.33,0:19:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,support for exporting and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.50,0:19:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,importing string dics file
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.01,0:19:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,formats.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.52,0:19:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So string dics is the powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,tool that lets you handle
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.99,0:19:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,plurals and adaptive strings in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.00,0:19:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.12,0:19:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In Xcode 9 you can now add and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.65,0:19:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,create string dictionaries right
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from the file template list in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode and that will generate an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.93,0:19:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,editor for you where you can add
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.04,0:19:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and edit your keys and values.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.60,0:19:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So now let's talk more in detail
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.45,0:19:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,about what can you do with
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.80,0:19:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,strings dictionaries and why
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,they are helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So first strings dictionaries
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.51,0:19:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,can help you handle the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.37,0:19:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,complexity of plural forms
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.97,0:19:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,without writing any code in your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.56,0:19:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.20,0:20:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's assume I have this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.24,0:20:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,logic in my code to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.23,0:20:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,plural variants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.56,0:20:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So here I have an array.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.56,0:20:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If the count of my array is one
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.60,0:20:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I set my string to one popular
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.90,0:20:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,language.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Else if the count of my array is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.43,0:20:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,more than one I set my string
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.42,0:20:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,here to something like person d
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.01,0:20:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,popular languages where person d
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is a format string that will
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.58,0:20:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,replace the runtime with the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.18,0:20:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,count of my array.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.91,0:20:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So this logic might work -- well
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.17,0:20:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it would work for a language
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.92,0:20:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,like English where there are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.39,0:20:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,only two plural forms; one
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.10,0:20:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,singular and one plural.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.39,0:20:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But this would be a complete
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.63,0:20:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,disaster for a language like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.63,0:20:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Russian where there are more
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.05,0:20:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,plural variants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.55,0:20:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So Russian has four different
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.06,0:20:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,plural variants and your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.76,0:20:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,translators need to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,work arounds and ways on how to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,translate all these variants
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.54,0:20:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with the one generic plural that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.75,0:20:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you provided -- the one you are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.89,0:20:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,using for English, which will
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.81,0:20:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,make basically your translations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.26,0:20:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sound robotic and not very
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.63,0:20:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,natural for a native speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.52,0:21:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So this example here sounds like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.01,0:21:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,something; "popular languages
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.64,0:21:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,column one, popular languages
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.17,0:21:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,column two," and you don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.31,0:21:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So to solve this kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.52,0:21:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,problem, when we're done writing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.44,0:21:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,any code you can just use
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.39,0:21:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,strings dictionaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.25,0:21:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So all you need to do in your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,strings dics file -- so you need
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.82,0:21:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to add your localized format
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.19,0:21:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,key.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.30,0:21:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In this example my localized
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.88,0:21:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,format key is "languages."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.99,0:21:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you need to add the plural
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.57,0:21:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,variants that are relevant for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.26,0:21:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your development language.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.76,0:21:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So since here my development
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.18,0:21:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,language is English, I only care
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.94,0:21:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,about two plural variants, one
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.25,0:21:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So one is for the singular case
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.19,0:21:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and other is for the plural
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.74,0:21:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.53,0:21:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then by wrapping your plural
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.71,0:21:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,string with NS Localized String,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.83,0:21:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as you will do with any other
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.42,0:21:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,string that you have in your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.45,0:21:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,code, when you export your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:21:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,projects for localization, Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.05,0:21:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,will generate automatically for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.13,0:22:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you the plural keys for other
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.05,0:22:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,languages that you support.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.82,0:22:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So the variance for other
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.58,0:22:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,languages will be included in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.13,0:22:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,your XK files and your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.93,0:22:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,translators when they are
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.02,0:22:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,translating the strings they
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.50,0:22:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,will find the plural variants
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.26,0:22:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that are relevant for the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.54,0:22:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,language.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.60,0:22:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And now our translation will be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.17,0:22:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,correct and your users will have
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.74,0:22:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,more grammatically correct
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.30,0:22:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,translations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.76,0:22:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is Strings Dics support
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.44,0:22:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for Plural Variants in Xcode 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.11,0:22:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing you can do with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.78,0:22:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,strings dictionaries in Xcode 9
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is support for adaptive strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.46,0:22:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we take this example from
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.58,0:22:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ia's app earlier, she had a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.32,0:22:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,string here called "Gross
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.24,0:22:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Domestic Products in Billions,"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.70,0:22:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is kind of long, but it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.07,0:22:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,fits fine on an iPad because
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.41,0:22:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,there is enough space for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.64,0:22:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If we run the app again in a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.37,0:22:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller device like an iPhone 7
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.44,0:22:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-- so this string does not fit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.72,0:22:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.31,0:22:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see on the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.62,0:22:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the number on the right side now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.99,0:22:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,shrinks and you can only read
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.57,0:22:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the three first characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.61,0:23:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which is kind of wrong because
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.77,0:23:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we are given the wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.49,0:23:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,information to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.71,0:23:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.19,0:23:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,strings dictionaries again to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.87,0:23:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,solve these kinds of problems
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.48,0:23:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and provide different string
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.00,0:23:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,variants for your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.17,0:23:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So here I have three different
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.51,0:23:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,keys; 20, 25, and 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.37,0:23:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They correspond to different
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.56,0:23:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,screen sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.34,0:23:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I have the strings that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.59,0:23:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to show for every screen
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.25,0:23:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,size.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.35,0:23:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you call NS Localized
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.68,0:23:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Strings on the key within your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,strings dics file.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.39,0:23:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So you enable -- we pick the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.71,0:23:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,right value for you at runtime
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.20,0:23:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the space available on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.27,0:23:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.86,0:23:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you are not using UI label
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.60,0:23:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are using a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.61,0:23:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,control of your own, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.63,0:23:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,still take advantage of the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.20,0:23:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality by calling
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.24,0:23:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,variance fit in presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.93,0:23:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with API, where you pass in one
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.48,0:23:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the keys that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.50,0:23:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,defined in your strings dics
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.15,0:23:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,file and then at runtime this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.96,0:23:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will choose the right value for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.45,0:23:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you that corresponds to that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.75,0:23:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,key.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.65,0:24:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will be providing the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.70,0:24:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,keys and the corresponding
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.19,0:24:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,screen sizes in the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.27,0:24:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,documentation if you would like
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.76,0:24:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to check out that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.05,0:24:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So now if we run again the app
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.35,0:24:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,on the iPad, still using the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.04,0:24:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,full string, and if we run it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.56,0:24:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,again in a smaller device like
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.20,0:24:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,an iPhone 7 now we pick the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.23,0:24:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,right variant that will fit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.72,0:24:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,nicely on the screen size.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.29,0:24:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus without erasing a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.40,0:24:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,single line of code your app
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.95,0:24:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,looks nice and beautiful in all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.20,0:24:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,different screen sizes and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.53,0:24:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,configurations of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.32,0:24:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And adaptive strings are really
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.78,0:24:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful if you are supporting
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.50,0:24:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,localizations in your app
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.86,0:24:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because you might have some
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.90,0:24:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,languages that are longer or
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.47,0:24:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,shorter than others and you want
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.06,0:24:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to give this flexibility to your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.43,0:24:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,translators to provide like
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.50,0:24:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,adaptive strings for the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.69,0:24:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,language.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.94,0:24:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that you're done with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.27,0:24:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,supporting plural support as
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.32,0:24:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,well as adaptive strings you are
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.29,0:24:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ready to localize your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.56,0:24:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first step in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.52,0:24:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,localization is exporting your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.93,0:24:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,project.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.01,0:24:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you export your projects
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.33,0:25:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for localization -- so Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.13,0:25:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will ask you which languages you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.44,0:25:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,want to localize first.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.01,0:25:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you pick the language
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.51,0:25:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you want Xcode will generate
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.53,0:25:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,XLIFF files for you to send to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.19,0:25:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,your translators.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.24,0:25:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So once your XLIFF files are
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.64,0:25:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,translated you can import them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.03,0:25:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,back in your project and Xcode
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.20,0:25:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,will show you this nice diff
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.93,0:25:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with what was changed by your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.93,0:25:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,translators.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.18,0:25:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that Xcode will just
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.05,0:25:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,integrate your localized text
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.58,0:25:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,back into your project and your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.14,0:25:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,strings will be localized.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.44,0:25:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that your strings are
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.62,0:25:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,localized, what about other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.13,0:25:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,resources that are not string
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.64,0:25:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,based that you want -- probably
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.99,0:25:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to localize, like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,images or audio files?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.66,0:25:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So you might have something like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.04,0:25:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this, an image that has text on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.37,0:25:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it, and you want to provide an
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.14,0:25:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,alternative image for other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.57,0:25:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.62,0:25:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can localize other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.54,0:25:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,resources in Xcode easily by
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.87,0:25:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,clicking the "localize" button
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.35,0:25:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the "file inspector."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.34,0:25:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Again Xcode will ask you which
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.36,0:25:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,language you want to localize
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.58,0:26:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this asset for.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.43,0:26:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pick from the list of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.15,0:26:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your languages and Xcode will
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.43,0:26:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,move this asset to the specific
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.44,0:26:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,language folder where you can
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.33,0:26:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,replace it with the image or the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.00,0:26:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,asset that you want to show for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.55,0:26:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that language.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.17,0:26:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the localization
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.76,0:26:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,workflow in Xcode 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.65,0:26:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we saw how to support plurals
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.28,0:26:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as adaptive strings and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.06,0:26:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,how to localize other resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.01,0:26:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.33,0:26:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,call Chris on stage to give you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.26,0:26:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.59,0:26:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.02,0:26:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.25,0:26:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.92,0:26:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.02,0:26:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.24,0:26:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So earlier we saw Ia validate
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.56,0:26:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that her app as
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.14,0:26:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalized using both our
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.21,0:26:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,framework and tools features.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.28,0:26:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get started on actually
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.46,0:26:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,localizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.97,0:26:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,First though, I really
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.04,0:26:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,appreciated Sarah's discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.53,0:26:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of plurals and adaptive width
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.96,0:26:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.21,0:26:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've added a strings dict
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.87,0:27:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,file to our project here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.69,0:27:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops. [laughs]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.14,0:27:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've added that GDP adaptive
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.04,0:27:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,width string with all of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.12,0:27:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,different variants for our
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.66,0:27:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,different device widths; 20, 25,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.51,0:27:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.20,0:27:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've also created a plural
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.00,0:27:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,variant, just like Sarah showed,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.89,0:27:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for the number of popular
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.30,0:27:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.65,0:27:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now though, I'm ready to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.84,0:27:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,localize my application into
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.79,0:27:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.16,0:27:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I'm going to do is go to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.59,0:27:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the project editor and right
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.00,0:27:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,under my localizations, where it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.86,0:27:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,tells me that English is my
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.02,0:27:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,development language, I have
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.55,0:27:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this plus button.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.75,0:27:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can choose that and just go
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.35,0:27:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about halfway down and choose
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.04,0:27:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.13,0:27:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And Xcode will ask me which of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.99,0:27:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,my resources I want to take and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.12,0:27:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,make Russian placeholders for.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.37,0:28:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I want to localize
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.54,0:28:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,everything I'm just going to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.07,0:28:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,tell Xcode to finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.59,0:28:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see that in addition
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.55,0:28:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to my main storyboard file I now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.90,0:28:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,have a placeholder for my
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.75,0:28:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Russian strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.05,0:28:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Still in the project editor, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.80,0:28:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,going to go to the "editor" menu
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.03,0:28:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,now and I'm going to export my
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.68,0:28:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,project for localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.63,0:28:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just going to save this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.86,0:28:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,file -- actually this folder --
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.20,0:28:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on the desktop and Xcode is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.28,0:28:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,going to read through all of my
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.52,0:28:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,source code, all of my
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.61,0:28:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,resources, and it's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.23,0:28:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,generate that XLIFF file.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.27,0:28:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at what it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.63,0:28:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.07,0:28:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you can see that the file
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.91,0:28:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is named "ru.xliff" where ru is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.39,0:28:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the ISO language code for the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.03,0:28:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Russian language.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.26,0:28:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I double click this we
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.30,0:28:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,have a little tool that we've
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.29,0:28:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,written so that we can see all
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.45,0:28:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of this localization data in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.08,0:29:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a tabular form so that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.40,0:29:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't have to wade through a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.46,0:29:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,whole bunch of XML angle
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.63,0:29:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,brackets just to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.90,0:29:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And up at the top here you can
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.70,0:29:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,see a bunch of strings that came
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.45,0:29:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,directly from our storyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.79,0:29:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,file.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.61,0:29:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see in our
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.89,0:29:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,translation column everything is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.30,0:29:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in red because we haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.33,0:29:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,actually put any translations in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.40,0:29:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,this XLIFF file yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.91,0:29:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in the next section we have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.18,0:29:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,file -- we have elements that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.07,0:29:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,will go into our localized
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.97,0:29:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,strings -- our
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.89,0:29:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable.stringsdict file.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.17,0:29:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see that there are
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.63,0:29:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,more variants of the percent d
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.53,0:29:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,popular languages string than we
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.78,0:29:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,had in our original
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.14,0:29:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable.stringsdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.58,0:29:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is because Xcode knows
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.36,0:29:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're exporting to Russian
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.10,0:29:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and creates placeholders for all
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.72,0:29:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Russian variants for you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.27,0:29:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.56,0:29:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have our adaptive width
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.43,0:29:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,string variants for the gross
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.76,0:30:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,domestic product and we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.17,0:30:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,couple other things like our
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.68,0:30:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,application name and our
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.64,0:30:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,info.plist and the strings from
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.73,0:30:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,our source code that will then
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.81,0:30:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,show up in a Russian
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.89,0:30:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable.strings file upon
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.32,0:30:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,import.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.64,0:30:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's say I have a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.59,0:30:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,translator who worked really
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.06,0:30:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,fast and I have a translated
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.94,0:30:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,version of this XLIFF ready to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.68,0:30:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.92,0:30:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I could just go to the project
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.18,0:30:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,editor in Xcode and choose
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.88,0:30:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"import localizations" and just
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.50,0:30:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,choose that file and export --
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.22,0:30:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode will read your project,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.80,0:30:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,read the file, and then show you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.21,0:30:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,how what that file is importing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.25,0:30:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,differs from your project.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.70,0:30:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I'm just getting a warning
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.83,0:30:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that I didn't actually localize
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.59,0:30:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of my app in English
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.64,0:30:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,yet, but I do have a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.08,0:30:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,localization now in Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.71,0:30:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can also see in the files
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.03,0:30:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,view here exactly what files
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.53,0:30:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will be affected by this import.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.73,0:31:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is all what I expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.44,0:31:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I tell Xcode to import it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.97,0:31:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and it'll write out these new
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.08,0:31:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,resource files for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.34,0:31:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see that where we
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.63,0:31:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't have a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.40,0:31:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable.strings file before,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.90,0:31:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,now we have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.29,0:31:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I choose it we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.26,0:31:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable.strings file with a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.35,0:31:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,whole bunch of Russian text.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.71,0:31:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if I run our application --
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.45,0:31:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like I've hit a little
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.75,0:31:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,bug here, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.19,0:31:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops. I'll just quit and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.18,0:31:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,relaunch Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.31,0:31:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if I run our application
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.81,0:31:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we're building and Xcode is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.40,0:31:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,integrating all of our
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.23,0:31:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,localizable strings that we just
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.74,0:31:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,imported.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.21,0:31:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one step that I missed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.75,0:31:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,though, sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:32:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to run my application in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.26,0:32:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Russian so I can see those
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.58,0:32:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,translations.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.35,0:32:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm just going to open the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.11,0:32:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,scheme editor and I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.73,0:32:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,switch from that right to left
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.89,0:32:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pseudo language that I was using
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.08,0:32:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Russian language.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.88,0:32:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And now if I run our application
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.77,0:32:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll build the storyboard, copy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.49,0:32:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the swift standard libraries,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.51,0:32:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.96,0:32:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can see our application
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.25,0:32:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is running in Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.67,0:32:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And not only are all the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.08,0:32:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,formatters and everything
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.38,0:32:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,correct for all of our dates and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.50,0:32:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,our numbers, but we also have
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.93,0:32:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,all of that Russian text that we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.23,0:32:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just imported.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.24,0:32:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to summarize, strings dicts
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.47,0:32:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,are really powerful and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.18,0:32:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,use them for pluralization and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.43,0:32:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for adaptive width strings in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.28,0:32:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,your applications to ensure that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.02,0:33:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,they look right not only based
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.33,0:33:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,on the user's language, but also
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.04,0:33:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,based on their device width.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.17,0:33:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy to export an XLIFF
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.32,0:33:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from your Xcode application for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.46,0:33:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,your localization process and to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.58,0:33:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,import your translated strings
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.36,0:33:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,via XLIFF back into your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.40,0:33:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,application's Xcode project.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.88,0:33:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And Sarah showed us how you can
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.59,0:33:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,also localize non-string
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.75,0:33:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,resources in Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.89,0:33:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And now Ia is going to show us
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.03,0:33:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,how you can test your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.45,0:33:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,localization.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.52,0:33:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.05,0:33:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Chris.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.58,0:33:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe that my app is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.41,0:33:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,already localized into its first
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.97,0:33:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,language and the steps were
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.46,0:33:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,really simple and easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.52,0:33:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.07,0:33:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that I do have my
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.56,0:33:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,localization, let's talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.29,0:33:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,some things that we could do to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.52,0:33:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,test it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.44,0:33:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,New in Xcode 9 we've introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.59,0:34:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability to specify the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.36,0:34:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,application language and region
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.53,0:34:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would like to run your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.56,0:34:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,tests in.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.71,0:34:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do this in the test
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.17,0:34:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,scheme editor right in Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.36,0:34:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And today I want to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.50,0:34:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,UI testing with XC test.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.09,0:34:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So UI testing is a great way for
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.23,0:34:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you to validate both your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.50,0:34:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,application's UI as well as its
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.45,0:34:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.34,0:34:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take this line of code on
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.33,0:34:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the screen for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.47,0:34:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what you would write to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.67,0:34:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,simulate tapping on a table cell
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.89,0:34:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that has the text territory in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.24,0:34:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.17,0:34:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's not going to work for
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.71,0:34:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,localization because that text
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.87,0:34:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to be translated into
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.53,0:34:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,each language that you run your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.86,0:34:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,test in.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.04,0:34:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And additionally, if you decide
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.48,0:34:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to go and change the wording in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.73,0:34:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,your app, even in your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.84,0:34:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,development language -- like
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.30,0:34:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say I want to call it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.29,0:34:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"region" now instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.36,0:34:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"territory," you don't really
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.09,0:34:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,want to go back and update every
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.93,0:34:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,single test that you've written
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.53,0:34:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,just so that it can start
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.87,0:34:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,succeeding again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.54,0:34:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead, what we recommend
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.14,0:34:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you do is use accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.73,0:34:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.77,0:35:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These identifiers are unique to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.38,0:35:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,every element on your screen and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.46,0:35:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use them to find these
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.62,0:35:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,elements without really knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.01,0:35:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what strings are loaded into
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.89,0:35:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.05,0:35:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So to set the accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.53,0:35:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier, you can simply set
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.41,0:35:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the property on your UI control
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.30,0:35:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when create it, or your NS
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.92,0:35:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,control.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.09,0:35:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if you're loading your UI
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.73,0:35:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,from a storyboard or a zip file
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.61,0:35:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you can set it in the identity
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.02,0:35:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,inspector in interface builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.23,0:35:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that your tests are
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.73,0:35:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,localization friendly and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.02,0:35:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they're succeeding in all the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.57,0:35:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,languages that you support,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.78,0:35:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,there's even more that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.18,0:35:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,do to take advantage of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.91,0:35:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're introducing -- this year
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.44,0:35:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we're introducing XCT attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.01,0:35:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs, which allow you to attach
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.23,0:35:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,screen shots as well as any
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.00,0:35:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,other data you collect during
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.62,0:35:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,your test and it'll attach it to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.59,0:35:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your test report at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.77,0:35:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What this empowers you to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.35,0:36:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,get a full coverage of your UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.91,0:36:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So every screen in your app, in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.89,0:36:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,every localization that you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.24,0:36:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,support, as well as every device
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.73,0:36:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that you support.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.70,0:36:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do all that while
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.12,0:36:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,writing only one test -- well,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.95,0:36:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one test for each thing you want
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.94,0:36:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to test.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.14,0:36:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughing] To find out more
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.94,0:36:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about XCT attachment and what
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.26,0:36:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,else is new in testing please
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.40,0:36:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,see those related sessions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.95,0:36:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.64,0:36:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I want to show you a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.98,0:36:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,test that I've written for my
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.41,0:36:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,international facts app.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.53,0:36:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So in my Xcode project
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.28,0:36:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already created this UI
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.93,0:36:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,test target and I wrote my first
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.36,0:36:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,test, called Test Some
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.57,0:36:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.87,0:36:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's run it to see what it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.19,0:36:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,does exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.28,0:37:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Xcode will launch my test
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.99,0:37:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,runner, which in turn launches
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.09,0:37:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.78,0:37:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this specific test we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.20,0:37:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,select a different territory, in
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.74,0:37:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this case Belgium, and then the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.67,0:37:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,test succeeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.74,0:37:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So now let's try running my test
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.05,0:37:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.79,0:37:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that I'll go into my
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.69,0:37:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,scheme and instead of "run" this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.46,0:37:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,time we want to select "test"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.65,0:37:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and under language I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.27,0:37:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,choose "Russian" so I can test
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.97,0:37:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the new localization that Chris
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.93,0:37:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,added to my project.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.05,0:37:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now again my test runner
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.30,0:37:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,launches, which launches my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.40,0:37:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time my app is launched
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.86,0:37:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in Russian, but it looks like my
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.73,0:37:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,test failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.08,0:37:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.80,0:37:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks like my test can't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.62,0:37:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,find a cell that has "territory"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.57,0:37:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in it, which is what we just
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.62,0:37:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,talked about.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.70,0:38:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Silly me. So -- oops, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.05,0:38:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So in my project I'm going to go
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.44,0:38:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,back to my main table view
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.07,0:38:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,controller and make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.42,0:38:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm setting an accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.65,0:38:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier for my territory
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.88,0:38:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,picker cell so I can actually
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.67,0:38:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,select it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.78,0:38:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I create my cell I also
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.61,0:38:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,want to give it an identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.30,0:38:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So territory picker cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.60,0:38:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to use the same
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.96,0:38:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier in my test.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.64,0:38:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So where it's failing, instead
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.30,0:38:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of using static text I'll simply
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.32,0:38:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,replace it with this identifier
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.50,0:38:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that I just created.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.11,0:38:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'll try to run my test
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.48,0:38:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,again in Russian using the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.66,0:38:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.08,0:39:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, my app launches
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.05,0:39:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in Russian again, but this time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.61,0:39:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it actually got further and it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.54,0:39:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,chose Belgium as the country and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.42,0:39:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the text succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.41,0:39:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just want to show you what
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.53,0:39:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,my test does exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.38,0:39:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I want to validate some
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.66,0:39:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of -- some functionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.84,0:39:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have this XCT assert equal
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.86,0:39:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that my app
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.46,0:39:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,initially launches with the US
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.50,0:39:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,selected and then I use the XCT
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.47,0:39:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment APIs to collect
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.95,0:39:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,screen shots.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.69,0:39:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So my first screen shot is a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.76,0:39:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,screen shot of the US page.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.32,0:39:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And I add it to my test case and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.57,0:39:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then I collect more screen shots
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.19,0:39:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,later when I open the territory
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.79,0:39:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,list and after I've selected
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.55,0:39:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Belgium.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.03,0:39:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And now finally if I want to see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.77,0:39:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,these attachments I can simply
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.88,0:39:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,go to the "reports" navigator in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.89,0:39:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the sidebar and select my most
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.10,0:39:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,recent test that I've run.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.00,0:39:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then if I expand my test
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.72,0:39:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,some territories test case,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.45,0:39:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see that some of these
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.67,0:40:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,lines have the attachment icon
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.63,0:40:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.54,0:40:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the attachments
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.81,0:40:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've created.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.19,0:40:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So as I've mentioned, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.01,0:40:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all screen shots in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.07,0:40:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's so much that I can
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.86,0:40:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,do with these attachments.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.54,0:40:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can bundle them up and send
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.08,0:40:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,them to somebody to ensure the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.43,0:40:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of my translations,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.05,0:40:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody who actually speaks
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.19,0:40:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,these different localizations --
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.92,0:40:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make sure the UI looks
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.52,0:40:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,good and the formatters are
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.86,0:40:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.17,0:40:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can even use these screen
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.15,0:40:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,shots in my app store preview
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.77,0:40:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,when I want to launch my app in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.35,0:40:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all these different storefronts
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.63,0:40:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,around the world so that users
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.43,0:40:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,can get a preview of what your
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.82,0:40:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,app will look like in their
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.75,0:40:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,language.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.48,0:40:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I show you how with one test
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.61,0:40:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you can test every single
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.64,0:40:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,localization that you add in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.19,0:40:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.36,0:40:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And to summarize what we talked
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.82,0:40:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,about today, we covered the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.04,0:40:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,localization process for an app.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.43,0:40:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you need to prepare your
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.02,0:41:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,code for localization, and
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.56,0:41:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the internationalization
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.89,0:41:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.15,0:41:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we showed you ways you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.06,0:41:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,can validate your apps readiness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.30,0:41:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,including the static analyzer
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.59,0:41:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and auto layout warnings and the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.35,0:41:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,new pseudo languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.98,0:41:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can export your --
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.64,0:41:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,all your localizable content
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.14,0:41:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,into a single XLIFF.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.84,0:41:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that includes string
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.24,0:41:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,dict files, which are really
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.67,0:41:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful for handling plurals
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.54,0:41:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and adaptive strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.04,0:41:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, when your XLIFF is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.73,0:41:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,translated you can import it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.68,0:41:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,back into your project and that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.33,0:41:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,integrates the translations into
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.03,0:41:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all the different pieces of your
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.50,0:41:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.33,0:41:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can take advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.66,0:41:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of your existing tests to run
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.90,0:41:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,them in all your supported
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.78,0:41:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,localizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.86,0:41:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.11,0:41:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the new XCT attachments to do a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.90,0:41:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,lot more than test your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.27,0:41:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.61,0:41:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information, our
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.80,0:41:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,session is 401, and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.56,0:41:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,visit our page on
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.31,0:41:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,developer.apple.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.61,0:42:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We highly recommend that you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.11,0:42:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,attend, or at least watch, these
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.50,0:42:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,related sessions throughout the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.82,0:42:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,week.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.73,0:42:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you and enjoy the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.56,0:42:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.52,0:42:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
